  /**
   * Given an integer array nums, we can select any subarray nums[l..r] and increase every element
   * in that subarray by an arbitrary positive integer x.
   * Return the minimum possible sum of all chosen x values to make the array non-decreasing.
   *
   * @param nums The input array of integers.
   * @return The minimum sum of x values.
   */
  def nums(nums: Array[Long]): Long = {
    var totalXSum: Long = 0
    for (i <- 0 until nums.length - 1) {
      if (nums(i) > nums(i + 1)) {
        // We need nums[i] <= nums[i+1] after operations.
        // Let the final values be nums'[i] and nums'[i+1].
        // nums'[i] = nums[i] + sum_of_x_applied_to_i
        // nums'[i+1] = nums[i+1] + sum_of_x_applied_to_i+1
        // We need nums[i] + S_i <= nums[i+1] + S_{i+1}
        // where S_i and S_{i+1} are the total increments applied to nums[i] and nums[i+1] respectively.

        // To satisfy the condition locally with minimum total added value,
        // we only need to ensure that the relative difference is covered.
        // If nums[i] > nums[i+1], the required increase for nums[i+1] relative to nums[i]
        // must be at least nums[i] - nums[i+1].

        // The problem asks for the minimum sum of x values across all operations.
        // Consider the difference d = nums[i] - nums[i+1] > 0.
        // We need to apply a total increment of at least d to nums[i+1] relative to nums[i].
        // This can be achieved by an operation that covers [i+1...r] and a smaller operation
        // that covers [i...r'] where r' < i+1 (which is impossible if we are only looking at i and i+1).

        // Key insight from similar problems: The minimum sum of x's is the sum of all positive
        // differences (nums[i] - nums[i+1]) for all i where nums[i] > nums[i+1].

        // If we apply an operation with x=d to the subarray [i+1..n-1],
        // then nums[i+1] becomes nums[i+1] + d.
        // nums[i+1] + d = nums[i+1] + (nums[i] - nums[i+1]) = nums[i].
        // This satisfies nums'[i] <= nums'[i+1] (since nums'[i] is unchanged by this op).
        // The cost of this operation is d.

        // If we sum up all such required differences:
